  "body": "The javadoc.io site is down and recovered but may have issues again.\r\nPlus now that we migrated jars to Cloudsmith, it's not updating as javadoc.io is only Maven or Bintray.\r\n\r\nHosting Javadoc on our own (in the doc site or on a separated github pages) may be a better solution.\r\n\r\n## Github pages\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n- can be published for each Besu CI build directly on Besu repos gh-pages\r\n- easy\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n- still another doc site to link from the Besu doc.\r\n- requires to provide custom templates to make users able to navigate between versions as it's already the case for javadoc.io\r\n\r\nThis would require at least:\r\n- [ ] create a gh-pages branch and activate the hosting in the repos settings\r\n- [ ] Modify CI to publish the javadoc to a gh-pages branch\r\n\r\nOptional version handling (otherwise only latest):\r\n- [ ] update gradle tasks for publishing javadoc in a folder for each version plus a latest and stable folder.\r\n- [ ] Create a system to have version navigation (i'm vague on this on purpose not to force a specific way to achieve this)\r\n\r\n## Integrated in the doc site\r\n\r\nPros:\r\n- can be published for each Besu CI build\r\n- would make the user experience for navigation even better than today as they would not leave the doc site.\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n- Requires the Besu CI build to push a PR to the doc.\r\n- requires to modify doc site templates for javadoc specific content inclusion.\r\n\r\nThis would require:\r\n- [ ] Modify CI to publish the javadoc to a doc repos dir with a PR.\r\n- [ ] Modify MkDocs templates to be able to display pages that includes already rendered HTML, make sure links are translated,...",
